Effective Date: 31/01/2025

At Custom Story, we care about your privacy and are committed to protecting the personal information of children who use our app. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it when you or your child use our Kids Stories Application. By using our app, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect

We collect different types of information when users interact with our app. The types of information collected include:

Personal Information: We do not ask for or collect personal information such as your child's name, email address, phone number, or physical address through the app.
Non-Personal Information: We may collect non-personal data, such as device type, operating system, app usage statistics, and preferences. This information is used to improve the app experience and performance.
2. How We Use Information

We use the information we collect to provide, improve, and personalize the experience within our app. Specifically, we may use the information to:

Improve app features and performance.
Provide personalized content recommendations (e.g., stories).
Respond to inquiries or feedback submitted through the app.
Monitor app usage and analyze trends to make our app better.

3. Data Storage & Security

We are committed to protecting the data and privacy of all users, including children. All data collected through the app is stored securely and is only accessible to authorized personnel. We use industry-standard encryption and security practices to protect your child’s information.

4. Third-Party Services

We may use third-party services such as analytics tools to help us understand how the app is being used and how we can improve it. These services may collect anonymous information about app usage, but they do not collect personal information. We do not allow third-party ads in the app to ensure a safe and ad-free experience for kids.

5. No Collection of Personal Data for Marketing

We do not collect or share any personal data for marketing purposes. Your child’s information will never be sold to third parties.

6. Parental Control and Access

Parents or guardians can contact us to request access to their child’s data, request to delete their child’s information, or ask any other questions regarding privacy. We are committed to ensuring that parents have control over the data associated with their children’s use of the app.

7. Children’s Privacy

This app is designed for children under the age of 13, and we comply with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA). We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13 without the consent of a parent or guardian.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes to the way we collect or use information, we will notify you within the app or via email. Please review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at:

fayzehalnabulsi@gmail.com
